<p>Scripting</p>

<p>Rename All files in directory to Lowercase</p>

<p>An elegant way to rename all files in a directory to lowercase</p>

<div class="language-plaintext highlighter-rouge"><div class="highlight"><pre class="highlight"><code>for i in `ls -1`; do mv $i "${i,,}" ; done
</code></pre></div></div>

<p>Explanation: There is a lower/upper case modification build-in bash using for, for looping files through directory.</p>

